    UnitListBoxExt

    public class UnitListBox
extends javax.swing.JList<Unit>
    The graphic user interface (GUI) component as list box JList shows the UnitList. Note, UnitList represents a list of many units; as a convention, it is called unit list. Recall objects in framework such as profile, item profile, user profile, rating matrix, interchanged attribute map are stored in archives (files) of entire framework. Each archive (file) is called unit representing a CSV file, database table, Excel sheet, etc. Unit is represented by Unit class. Your attention please, the list of default units is returned by the static method DataConfig.getDefaultUnitList(). In fact, important units such as rating unit, user profile, item profile, context are registered with DataConfig class as default units.

    This UnitListBox firstly connects with the store (directory or database) specified in the internal configuration config so as to retrieve list of units (retrieved UnitList) from such store. Later on, some units of the retrieved UnitList which are not in the default list returned by DataConfig.getDefaultUnitList() are marked as extra (auxiliary) units. Finally, this UnitListBox shows the retrieved UnitList.
